13
14 TO DESIGNATE THE MONTH OF FEBRUARY AS
15 NATIONAL CHILDREN'S DENTAL HEALTH MONTH.
16
17 WHEREAS, the future of the State of Arkansas is dependent to a large
18 extent on the good health of its families; and
19
20 WHEREAS, good health can be achieved in part through good dental habits
21 learned early and reinforced throughout life; and
22
23 WHEREAS, research shows that a balanced diet, proper oral hygiene, and
24 preventative dental care can prevent tooth decay and reduce dental-related
25 illnesses that cause school-aged children in the United States to miss
26 thirty-four million (34,000,000) school hours annually, starting as early as
27 grade one (1), lost hours that exacerbate socioeconomic disparities; and
28
29 WHEREAS, National Children's Dental Health Month is an opportunity for
30 the citizens of the State of Arkansas to unite and join in its observance in
31 order to raise public awareness about the importance of good oral health for
32 all children,
33
34 NOW THEREFORE,
35 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE NINETY-FIFTH GENERAL
36 ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
*ADF039*
